# Claims Triage Automation Dashboard

## Overview
An interactive Business Intelligence dashboard that automates the 
triage of Short-Term and Long-Term Disability (STD/LTD) claims using 
a rules-based logic engine built on fraud risk scoring, documentation 
completeness, prior claims history, and claim duration.

## The Problem
Traditional disability claims review treats every claim the same — 
every file goes through full manual review regardless of complexity. 
This creates backlog, delays benefits for straightforward claims, and 
buries senior examiners in low-risk files.

## The Solution
A triage automation model that categorizes claims into three pathways:
- ✅ Auto-Approve — Low fraud risk, complete documentation, clear policy coverage
- ⚡ Manual Review — Medium complexity, incomplete docs, or elevated risk factors
- 🚩 Investigate — High fraud score, pattern inconsistencies, escalated to senior examiner

## Features
- Interactive claims register with filter by claim type, triage outcome, and risk level
- Fraud risk scoring visualization with color-coded bar indicators
- Triage distribution donut chart
- Operational metrics including auto-approval rate and documentation completion rate
- Claims by medical condition mapped to triage outcomes
- Built-in triage logic documentation

## Tech Stack
- Data: Microsoft Excel + SQL queries
- Visualization: HTML, CSS, JavaScript
- Dataset: NJEA Sample Claims Dataset (14 STD/LTD claims)

## Key Metrics
- 35.7% Auto-Approve rate
- 28.6% High Risk flag rate  
- 57% of claims have incomplete documentation
- Average claim duration: 262 days

